Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.83,0:00:21.62,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,My left arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:24.10,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I still have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.04,0:00:27.28,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I went back again...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.28,0:00:30.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,No, maybe I should say I made it back...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.98,0:00:36.34,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry. Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.87,0:00:42.15,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Right, I guess you don't remember me...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.25,0:00:46.31,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the trouble I've caused!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.31,0:00:48.15,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki Subaru will now start over!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.00,0:00:53.18,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, what day and time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.81,0:02:27.25,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's my third first day in the Roswaal mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.54,0:02:30.12,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That chill I felt...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.12,0:02:33.54,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean I died in my sleep the \Nfirst time, due to physical weakness?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.41,0:02:35.88,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But the second time,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.48,0:02:38.13,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,there was an attacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.19,0:02:41.20,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So if I was killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.20,0:02:44.81,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,does that mean the others in \Nthe mansion are targets, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.81,0:02:48.43,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Because we're involved in Emilia's royal \Nselection, like at the loot house?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.00,0:02:50.47,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But even if I know that,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.47,0:02:55.55,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no proof to explain it \Nor any way to avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.55,0:02:58.44,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Worse yet, I didn't see the \Nattacker's face, or their prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.44,0:03:00.24,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,My death was totally in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.24,0:03:02.01,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,You're irritating me to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.01,0:03:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either stop it or be blown away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.68,0:03:07.34,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.34,0:03:11.53,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But somehow, walking in circles also \Nturns the gears in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.53,0:03:12.68,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Cut me some slack, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.68,0:03:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're tight, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.10,0:03:17.38,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly what sort of relationship do \Nyou think we have, I suppose?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.38,0:03:19.09,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,We've only met twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.64,0:03:25.36,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I won't make trouble for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.36,0:03:27.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Serve some tea or something, and let me relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.58,0:03:30.44,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,As if I'll serve you anything, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.44,0:03:32.23,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh, you're irritating me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.83,0:03:35.07,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What's that book you're reading?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.07,0:03:38.69,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,It explains how to get rid of bugs that \Nhave gotten into my room, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.90,0:03:42.72,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You've got bugs in the library? That sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.72,0:03:43.49,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of bugs?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.36,0:03:46.92,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for you to leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.92,0:03:48.60,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Your hands have stopped shaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.60,0:03:51.08,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,so you can mask your fear now, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.07,0:03:52.92,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You could tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.21,0:03:55.19,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,You were trying to hide it, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.19,0:03:58.33,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite vexing to be treated \Nas a mere convenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.73,0:04:01.02,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're not nice at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.02,0:04:02.56,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the help, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.56,0:04:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be counting on you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.02,0:04:06.24,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to be counted on, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.24,0:04:08.76,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,So don't come in here again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.09,0:04:10.47,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Shoo, shoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.75,0:04:12.83,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,"Shoo, shoo"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.36,0:04:16.03,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! When you said "bugs," you meant me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.03,0:04:18.07,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Just get out of here this instant!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.36,0:04:29.42,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I-If not for the flower bed, that would \Nhave been instant death...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.42,0:04:30.66,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.11,0:04:33.96,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Can I ask if you're all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.07,0:04:39.73,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia-tan, your kindness is the \None thing that can heal me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.73,0:04:44.18,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Rem just spread manure \Nin that flower bed yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.18,0:04:45.68,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Argh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.68,0:04:48.43,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Three-second rule! That didn't count... \NThat didn't count, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.42,0:04:54.70,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, they say this kind \Nof thing is actually lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.12,0:04:59.18,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia-tan is already shifting \Ninto consolation mode...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.23,0:05:02.53,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Puck, wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.73,0:05:10.37,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Lia...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.78,0:05:12.68,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Puck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.68,0:05:17.18,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to ask after you just woke up, \Nbut could you wash Subaru off?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.18,0:05:17.96,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.97,0:05:21.85,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll wash you off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.85,0:05:22.97,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.51,0:05:29.85,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,There, all clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.21,0:05:31.61,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.55,0:05:38.79,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was a goner...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.79,0:05:40.96,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't there another way to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.96,0:05:42.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You enjoyed that, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.63,0:05:46.11,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't true at all... Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.29,0:05:49.55,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Punch-backs!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.11,0:05:52.56,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you've done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:55.84,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Like that? It's my lethal move, \NMake the Cat Cry Ha Ha...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.84,0:05:57.04,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.33,0:05:58.54,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Tail punch!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:05:59.09,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.09,0:06:01.85,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll finish you with my paw-pad grind!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.50,0:06:04.34,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Grind, grind, grind, grind...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.07,0:06:09.90,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, gosh... Sorry, I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.90,0:06:11.70,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,What are you two doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.58,0:06:15.18,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my stomach... I'm dying...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.75,0:06:21.79,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, now that I've rebounded from \Nmy initial bad impression...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.79,0:06:23.62,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your assistance, Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.62,0:06:25.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you calling "Father"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.32,0:06:27.75,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I won't give you my daughter that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.75,0:06:30.76,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop. You're both too funny...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.31,0:06:33.72,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing beats your smile, Lia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.72,0:06:35.29,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,You agree, too. Right, Subaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.82,0:06:37.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I totally do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.64,0:06:42.46,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,To me, Emilia-tan's smile is the first \Nshining star in the night sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.87,0:06:45.05,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Not you, too, Subaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:48.05,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Also, what does "tan" mean? \NWhere'd it come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.96,0:06:52.73,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's what they call a pet name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.73,0:06:55.35,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Just like when Puck calls you "Lia."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.35,0:06:59.01,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's an expression of affection \Nthat shows people's closeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.68,0:07:03.31,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember getting so close to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.42,0:07:08.16,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That somewhat hurts, but I won't lose heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.16,0:07:10.49,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it as an advance on our relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.49,0:07:14.49,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It means I want us to get close enough \Nto call each other by pet names.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.49,0:07:14.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.01,0:07:23.24,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'll accept that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.07,0:07:26.67,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,No... Don't look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.66,0:07:31.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I expected her to cringe, \Nbut I got a positive response.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.59,0:07:33.22,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What could this mean, \NCommentator Puck-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.73,0:07:36.00,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't have many friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.00,0:07:38.32,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,so she craves things like nicknames.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.32,0:07:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's easy to please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.39,0:07:41.27,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,My main heroine is easy to please, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.94,0:07:44.51,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Sister, Sister... It's only been a short time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.51,0:07:46.91,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,and now our guest looks like a drowned rat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.91,0:07:49.44,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Rem, Rem. In just a short time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.44,0:07:51.77,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,our guest has turned into a dirty, old washrag.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.77,0:07:55.55,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm a rat. You don't have to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.55,0:07:59.29,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Our lord, Roswaal-sama, has returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.29,0:08:00.75,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Please come inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.47,0:08:03.25,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.80,0:08:06.40,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,My third first meeting with \Nthe lord of the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.48,0:08:13.34,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,All I know for certain is that someone \Nwill attack on the fourth night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.34,0:08:16.09,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be ideal if I could let them know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.09,0:08:18.64,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't explain where I got the information,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.86,0:08:21.94,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,so they might think I'm working \Nwith the assassin.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.94,0:08:24.74,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,If I just knew even the attacker's physique,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.74,0:08:26.23,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,it might be a different story.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.99,0:08:29.16,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So this time, I'll use these next four days
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.16,0:08:33.66,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,to gather information and \Nlearn who the attacker is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.66,0:08:35.07,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,And to do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.48,0:08:37.72,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,You may have any reward you request.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.72,0:08:41.20,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,Merely state your desire!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.58,0:08:42.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,In that case,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.98,0:08:44.60,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,let me live here as a house guest,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.60,0:08:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and eat and sleep all I want!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.54,0:08:58.00,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But how am I supposed to gather information?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.00,0:09:01.27,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll start with some \Nindirect questioning...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.24,0:09:05.94,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's where I fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.96,0:09:11.77,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.77,0:09:14.73,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. If you'll excuse me, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.73,0:09:15.74,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.33,0:09:18.41,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't even get a chance to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.76,0:09:26.78,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anything out of the ordinary...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.06,0:09:32.35,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,What do you not see?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.35,0:09:33.94,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Ros-chi...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.94,0:09:36.09,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't scare me like that. It's misleading.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.68,0:09:40.89,SignA,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Magic - died of weakness in sleep \NSound of chains \NRoswaal's chains X \NMisleading!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.42,0:09:44.93,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.06,0:09:47.74,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.74,0:09:50.68,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thanks. Want to drink it with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.68,0:09:52.71,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,No, thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.54,0:09:58.63,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you can be a little friendlier \Nto me if you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.02,0:10:06.08,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,642)}Well, it's my first day. \NI guess it makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.06,0:10:09.79,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.61,0:10:12.92,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Every day, you come in here \Nwithout even knocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.92,0:10:15.42,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,You truly have no manners whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.42,0:10:18.43,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Leaving would be in your best interest, \Nbefore you get blown away, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.77,0:10:20.28,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! Wait, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.28,0:10:22.05,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:27.84,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any magic that weakens and kills \Nsomeone, as if putting them to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.84,0:10:31.02,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,If I must answer, then yes, there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.76,0:10:32.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,There is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.91,0:10:36.32,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,But it isn't so much magic as \Nit is a curse, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.65,0:10:41.08,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,There are many such things among the \Nspells that shamans specialize in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.08,0:10:41.82,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Shamans?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.19,0:10:43.47,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Magicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.47,0:10:47.46,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,However, shamans are a subclass \Nof magic- and spirit-arts users,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.46,0:10:50.06,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,originating in the northern nation \Nof Gusteco, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.06,0:10:54.42,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,They're all quite useless, and not \Nto be taken seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.12,0:10:58.83,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,But there is an easier method \Nthan a curse, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.83,0:10:59.51,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Easier?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.56,0:11:03.84,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,I believe you've already experienced it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.45,0:11:06.43,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.17,0:11:10.77,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That mana drain you did against \Nmy will could actually kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.69,0:11:15.45,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Mana is also one's very life force.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.45,0:11:20.40,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,If you continually suck it out, one could \Ndie of weakness, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:23.95,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait... You're not the one \Nwho killed me, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.18,0:11:27.90,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to disappoint you, but I'm busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.90,0:11:31.22,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't even spare the effort to kill you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.21,0:11:33.72,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Is this what you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.75,0:11:36.21,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.21,0:11:37.29,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.29,0:11:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can anyone do that mana-sucking thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.12,0:11:43.28,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,That's an absolutely terrible \Nway to put it, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.28,0:11:45.45,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,In this mansion, only Bubby and I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.45,0:11:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Roswaal can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.55,0:11:50.76,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... It's actually a pretty rare skill, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.76,0:11:53.76,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't suck up that stuff too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.76,0:11:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.17,0:11:58.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really short on blood right now, \Nso I'd die in a heartbeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.63,0:12:01.20,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, all your organs were restored,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.20,0:12:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but your blood wasn't replaced, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.65,0:12:06.45,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I have no obligation to do so, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.81,0:12:07.87,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,My organs?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.29,0:12:11.88,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The way you said that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.88,0:12:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,makes it sound like you were the \None who healed my wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.50,0:12:19.38,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to take the credit from Emilia-tan \Nmakes you look bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.94,0:12:25.35,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,That silly girl doesn't have the power \Nto heal fatal wounds yet, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.35,0:12:26.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.14,0:12:30.64,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,She and Bubby stabilized you, \Nand I healed your wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.91,0:12:31.79,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.79,0:12:34.04,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,F-For real? You're kidding, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.97,0:12:36.51,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Of course... It's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.51,0:12:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a lie! It's not nice to lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.12,0:12:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No lying...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.53,0:12:43.16,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.16,0:12:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're too averse to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.77,0:12:47.29,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Someone not worth saving should \Ndisappear, I suppose!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.10,0:12:52.33,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.75,0:12:54.87,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Once again, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.64,0:13:00.04,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So, in the end, the key words \Nare "curse" and "chains."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.04,0:13:01.84,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.36,0:13:05.28,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,If Return by Death's conditions are the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.28,0:13:09.12,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I died three times in the capital, \Nand survived the fourth time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.12,0:13:13.20,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't mean I intend to \Ntreat this as a throwaway life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.20,0:13:17.10,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I asked Puck to keep \Nan eye on Emilia for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.88,0:13:19.19,Default - flashback,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.19,0:13:21.26,Default - flashback,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,This is all really vague,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.26,0:13:24.36,Default - flashback,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,765)}but I can tell you're asking \Nout of concern for Lia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.36,0:13:28.46,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,On the morning of the fourth day, \NI'll leave here and—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.82,0:13:29.58,SignA,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Magic - died of weakness in sleep \NSound of chains \NRoswaal's chains X \NMisleading!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.30,0:13:31.49,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon my intrusion, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.22,0:13:34.76,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I see you really are studying, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.76,0:13:37.09,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's super rude...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.09,0:13:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a guest here, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.32,0:13:42.51,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,You're a freeloader calling yourself a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.51,0:13:45.20,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I perceive it, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.20,0:13:46.43,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.72,0:13:50.93,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh, it's still nasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.93,0:13:55.40,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,You'll incur the wrath of the \Nmansion's finest tea leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.52,0:13:59.40,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Slacking off right in front of your guest?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.40,0:14:02.12,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I have no words for that nerve of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.12,0:14:05.93,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who told me to \Nbe more friendly toward you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.93,0:14:08.21,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only responding to your demand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.06,0:14:11.42,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,So? How is your studying coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.42,0:14:12.12,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Not bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.78,0:14:15.95,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I can read simple fairy tales like these now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.95,0:14:19.21,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's interesting how the morals slightly \Ndiffer from those of the ones I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.55,0:14:22.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's like true cross-cultural communication!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.32,0:14:25.92,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should import a few fairy \Ntales from my homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.92,0:14:27.81,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Like "The Red Ogre Who Cried."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.41,0:14:32.01,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,The Red Ogre Who Cried?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.24,0:14:34.85,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Want me to tell it to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.45,0:14:40.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,All right, your attention, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.23,0:14:47.11,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Once upon a time, there lived \Na red ogre and a blue ogre.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.74,0:14:50.66,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The two were very good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.51,0:14:55.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The red ogre wanted to be friends \Nwith the people of the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.47,0:14:59.99,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But the people were too scared \Nto get close to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.43,0:15:02.08,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The blue ogre couldn't bear to watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.08,0:15:04.88,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,so he devised a plan to help his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.74,0:15:10.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll make a ruckus in the village, \Nso you come and stop me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.14,0:15:13.53,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Then the villagers will be sure to trust you."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.20,0:15:18.52,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The plan worked, and the red \Nogre befriended the humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.99,0:15:23.31,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But as time passed, \Nsomething began to worry him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.98,0:15:28.19,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,His friend, the blue ogre, \Nno longer came to visit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.97,0:15:32.94,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,One day, the red ogre went \Nto the blue ogre's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.94,0:15:37.49,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The door was tightly shut, and a \Nletter was affixed to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.18,0:15:39.87,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The letter said...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.07,0:15:46.01,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,"Red Ogre-kun, please have fun \Nwith your human friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.54,0:15:49.52,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,If I continue to hang around you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.52,0:15:52.82,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,they might think you're a bad ogre, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.47,0:15:56.76,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So I've decided to go on a journey,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.76,0:15:59.81,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,but I will never forget you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.42,0:16:03.98,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye. Please take care of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.98,0:16:05.86,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Your friend forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.57,0:16:07.73,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Blue Ogre."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.85,0:16:12.99,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The red ogre read the letter in \Nsilence, over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.51,0:16:16.45,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Tears fell, as he began to cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.90,0:16:18.03,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The end.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.74,0:16:21.50,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,That's a sad story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.84,0:16:23.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.84,0:16:26.92,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But I think it's a sweet story, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.58,0:16:31.48,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I think all the characters in it are just stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.96,0:16:34.59,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,The red ogre, the blue ogre, \Nand the villagers, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.91,0:16:38.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's kind of a harsh critique.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.14,0:16:40.86,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, I'm not denying it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.86,0:16:44.73,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I both love and hate that story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:48.62,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The blue ogre's self-sacrifice\N is really appealing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.62,0:16:51.15,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,but it's stupid because \Nhe gets nothing in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.15,0:16:54.20,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the type that wants to be \Nrewarded for my effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.75,0:16:57.28,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you think of the blue ogre?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.37,0:17:00.91,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,But it's the red ogre that I think is beyond help.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.96,0:17:04.32,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,He dragged the blue ogre into his own desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.32,0:17:06.81,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, he lost nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.81,0:17:08.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the blue ogre lost anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.92,0:17:12.83,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do you think the two \Nogres should have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.30,0:17:16.74,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,If the red ogre truly wanted \Nto befriend the humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.74,0:17:19.22,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,he should have broken off his \Nhorns and gone to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.18,0:17:23.93,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,He should have done that before the \Nblue ogre couldn't bear to watch anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.30,0:17:28.05,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's a pretty extreme opinion, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.05,0:17:28.90,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.42,0:17:33.30,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Which of the two ogres would \Nyou rather be friends with?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.30,0:17:34.49,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Which of the two?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.86,0:17:40.33,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,The red ogre, who can only wish \Nand be taken care of by others,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.33,0:17:42.91,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,or the stupid blue ogre, \Nwho basks in self-sacrifice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.63,0:17:55.42,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,What a foolish answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.08,0:17:58.28,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to befriend both,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.28,0:18:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you must be the indecisive, adulterous type.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.01,0:18:02.36,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,You'll regret it one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.36,0:18:05.43,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I don't recall it being that kind of story!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.21,0:18:09.05,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Putting aside your homeland's fairy tales,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.05,0:18:11.74,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,did any of these stories leave \Nan impression on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.74,0:18:14.95,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the ones that interested me most
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.95,0:18:17.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,were the middle one, about the dragon,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.58,0:18:19.20,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,and at the end, about the witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.83,0:18:23.92,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I finally know where the name the "Dragon's \NKingdom of Lugunica" comes from.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.92,0:18:24.96,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.96,0:18:27.82,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It said the royal family signed \Na covenant with a dragon,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.82,0:18:30.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,so it's more like a folk tale \Nthan a fairy tale, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.14,0:18:33.39,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, since it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.89,0:18:38.57,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,The noble dragon still protects \Nthis nation from far away,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.57,0:18:40.97,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,beyond a great waterfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.58,0:18:45.28,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,It will do so until its contract with \Nthe royal family is fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.71,0:18:50.81,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, didn't the royal family that signed \Nthe contract recently die out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.81,0:18:52.69,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, quite abruptly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.51,0:18:56.49,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,No one knows what the dragon wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.98,0:19:00.82,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,In the nation's current situation, \Nonly the gods know...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.82,0:19:04.38,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,No, only the dragon knows what \Nthe dragon will do, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.34,0:19:08.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, by the way, about this witch story—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.86,0:19:10.83,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to discuss that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.41,0:19:12.67,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I've stayed too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.26,0:19:16.67,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come again to notify you \Nwhen dinner is ready, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.50,0:19:20.01,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.87,0:19:23.82,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,That story you told me about the ogres...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.82,0:19:25.64,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell it to Rem.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.64,0:19:27.97,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain she wouldn't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.38,0:19:39.69,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,"A scary witch, a terrifying witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.69,0:19:42.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,To even speak her name was terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.80,0:19:44.87,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone called her
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.60,0:19:47.44,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,the Jealous Witch."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.86,0:19:54.30,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.30,0:19:56.88,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,We could call a royal car to \Ntake you to the capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.20,0:19:59.20,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.20,0:20:04.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,One day, when I'm the kind of strong, \Nsmart, rich man who's worthy of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.14,0:20:05.97,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you away on a white horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.23,0:20:07.50,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a handkerchief?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.50,0:20:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And water, lagumite ore, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.62,0:20:12.26,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be able to sleep by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.26,0:20:13.60,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you're my mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.87,0:20:17.07,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Subaru-kun, be well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.07,0:20:19.07,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,And do not lose the gift I gave you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.52,0:20:23.45,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,I added something equivalent to our three \Ndays' worth of memories together...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.43,0:20:28.20,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Hush money, right? Don't worry, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.20,0:20:30.66,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I won't say anything I shouldn't. \NI swear to the dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.05,0:20:35.44,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,Talking with you makes any evil scheme \Nseem to lose its purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.87,0:20:40.67,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,And in this nation, swearing to the dragon \Nis the highest form of promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.04,0:20:43.09,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure not to forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.65,0:20:44.43,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.12,0:20:46.64,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You two helped me out a ton.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.43,0:20:50.64,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Especially you, Rem-rin. \NThanks for all the great food.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.64,0:20:52.27,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,And Ram-chi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.27,0:20:55.22,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! You're good at cleaning toilets, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.22,0:20:59.64,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Sister, Sister... Our guest is \Nhopelessly bad at flattery.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.64,0:21:03.20,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Rem, Rem... Our guest has a \Nfatal lack of skill in flattery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.20,0:21:04.27,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.27,0:21:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I seriously couldn't think of anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.51,0:21:09.12,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.58,0:21:10.34,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.42,0:21:18.50,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.95,0:21:21.55,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.55,0:21:23.38,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,If you need anything, come visit anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.08,0:21:25.90,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.30,0:21:30.97,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Emilia-tan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.37,0:21:52.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.55,0:21:56.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,From here, I can see Emilia's \Nroom especially well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.68,0:22:00.34,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Now all that's left is to wait \Nfor something to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.21,0:22:02.50,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,And stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.37,0:22:08.38,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,She'd probably get mad at me \Nfor using it this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.10,0:22:12.00,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I hope she does...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.01,0:22:15.81,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.04,0:22:19.73,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want them to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.26,0:22:25.49,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What did I tell you, Natsuki Subaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.18,0:22:30.10,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Even if no one remembers what \Nhappens when things repeat,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.10,0:22:32.45,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,you remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.70,0:22:40.52,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think about it, I didn't \Ngo shopping for Rem this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.18,0:22:43.42,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Just because the food \Nmeant for me was leftover?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.47,0:22:48.08,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It'll still be a while before dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.08,0:22:49.97,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Focus! Focus!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.49,0:23:04.27,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Emergency escape...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.00,0:23:05.57,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.88,0:23:06.86,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.36,0:23:09.31,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I saw where the sound of chains came from!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.73,0:23:11.96,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But is it coming this way now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.26,0:23:20.81,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Does this mean I played right \Ninto the attacker's hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.12,0:23:29.17,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,If you're coming, then come!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.76,0:23:38.35,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the nerve?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.56,0:23:45.37,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,All right... Show yourself, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.37,0:23:48.56,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I've gone through all kinds \Nof hell to see your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.90,0:24:05.21,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Then I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.02,0:24:19.22,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,The ideal scenario would have been to \Nfinish this without anyone noticing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.65,0:24:25.61,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're joking...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.84,0:24:27.92,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Rem?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.78,0:24:35.82,Episode Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,The Sound {\c&HCFA9F7&}of Chains
